HEADWORD: Upsilon
<hw>Up"si*lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'y^
psilo`n</grk> bare, mere, simple <ets>y</ets>.]</ety> <def>The 20th
letter (⟦UPSILON⟧, ⟦upsilon⟧) of the Greek alphabet, a vowel having
originally the sound of ⟦oomac⟧ as in <xex>room</xex>, becoming before
the 4th century <sc>b. c.</sc> that French <it>u</it> or Ger.
<it>⟦uum⟧.</it> Its equivalent in English is <it>u</it> or
<it>y</it>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

